Page.PageName: Step 2- Turn on Radiacmeter and Check Battery Status

Text.Value: The unit features two methods of communicating a low battery level. Turn on the unit by pressing the ON/OFF button.
• If the unit has 300 minutes or less of battery life remaining, a blinking 'BAT' will appear in the display
• To get the approximate battery life in minutes, press the CLR/TEST button
Whenever BAT is displayed, you should replace the batteries as soon as possible since the remaining batter life number is ONLY a very rough approximation.
• If a lower case blinking "b" is displayed, turn off the unit and replace the batteries as soon as possible

Pre-Operation Test Procedures

Check Battery Level

  • If the unit's batteries have 300 minutes or less useful life remaining, a blinking "BAT" will appear in the top left-hand corner of the display.
  • Press the CLR/TEST button to review the radiacmeter's remaining battery life.
  • A three-digit number will be displayed, indicating the approximate remaining battery life in minutes.
  • Whenever "BAT" is displayed, you should replace the batteries as soon as possible.
  • The remaining battery life number is ONLY a very rough approximation.
  • If a lower-case blinking "b" is displayed, indicating very low batteries, turn the unit off and replace the batteries as soon as possible.
